featured_reviews.review_id:
Panditain ki Masjid (or padain ki Masjid), Lucknow

This majestic 18th-century mosque was constructed by a Brahmin lady Rani Jai Kunwar Pandey for her beloved friend Khadijah Khanum. Khanum was the wife of the first Nawab of Awadh Amin Sa'adat Khan Burhan-ul-Mulk.

The Tomb of Khadijah Khanum was once situated on the land of this mosque but it couldn't survive the destruction caused to it during the first war of independence in 1857.  Though the indication of the grave of Khanum is still there.
The mosque is a combination of Awadhi, Rajasthani and Mughal architectural styles. The mosque is surrounded by many beautiful old buildings of Lucknow like Aiwan-e-Haider, Aditya Bhavan, etc.

The mosque is a well-maintained is situated in Aminabad,
